cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for combining the high predictive performance of deep neural networks with the high interpretability of linear models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The method is applied to both image and text classification tasks, indicating that computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories are also possible. Finally, the paper involves the use of sparse local linear models, which suggests that the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category may also be relevant.
